---
/**
 * production-ai-architecture/0001 · Figure 2 (Module 1) — the availability × quality
 * two-by-two; only the timely-and-correct quadrant is reliable.
 *
 * Verbatim copy of the source SVG (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote
 * <sup> #s2 / id="r2b"). Astro renders the kebab-case SVG attrs as plain HTML,
 * so it ships byte-for-byte. See Fig1 header for the why.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 260"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A two-by-two of availability versus quality: only the top-right quadrant where the answer is both timely and correct counts as reliable."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Reliable = timely AND correct-enough</text
        >
        <!-- axes -->
        <line x1="120" y1="60" x2="120" y2="210" stroke="#111110" stroke-width="1.2"></line>
        <line x1="120" y1="210" x2="560" y2="210" stroke="#111110" stroke-width="1.2"></line>
        <text x="120" y="46" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >quality &uarr;</text
        >
        <text x="560" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >availability &rarr;</text
        >
        <!-- quadrants -->
        <rect x="124" y="64" width="214" height="70" rx="6" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="231" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >correct but too slow</text
        >
        <text x="231" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >30s hang &rarr; user gone</text
        >
        <rect
            x="342"
            y="64"
            width="214"
            height="70"
            rx="6"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
        <text x="449" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >&#10003; timely + correct</text
        >
        <text x="449" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >the only reliable quadrant</text
        >
        <rect x="124" y="138" width="214" height="66" rx="6" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="231" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >slow + wrong</text
        >
        <text x="231" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">worst case</text>
        <rect x="342" y="138" width="214" height="66" rx="6" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="449" y="162" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >fast but wrong</text
        >
        <text x="449" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >200 OK · health check happy</text
        >
        <text x="449" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#9a2417"
            >user harmed, monitor silent</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A normal service only has the horizontal axis. The bottom-right quadrant — <em
            >fast but wrong</em
        > — is the one AI adds, and it's invisible to availability monitoring. You must set an SLO on
        <b>both</b> axes.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r2b">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
